Honestly I feel that wizards are balanced fine from a power <br>
standpoint, to that end you will not be receiving an upgrade <br>
to your damage output. <br>
<br>
<br>
Demented One Said<br>
You Have  Never Played a Wizard in your life Admit it.<br>
<br>
<br>
MR. Poe Said<br>
Where I do feel wizards need help is group utility. <br>
<br>
Demented One Said<br>
Oh Boy a New Spell Line to make us more like druids or enchanters, as if <br>
O'keits radition was not OverPowering enough.<br>
<br>
MR. Poe Said<br>
I've spent countless hours pondering a solution, I've read countless <br>
message board forums and emails looking at suggestions from you guys. <br>
Finally a solution was found! I'm not naive enough to believe that <br>
everyone <br>
will be happy about the new enhancement but this is an idea I've seen <br>
tossed around on a number of forums and I think not only does it fit in<br>
well with wizards being the masters of arcane transportation, I think <br>
it will make them very desirable in the 50 to 60 levels where they <br>
seem to be struggling for usefulness. <br>
The new spells will give wizards the ability to prevent NPCs from <br>
gating. There will be 3 versions of the spells starting at level 51. <br>
They will each have a different resistance type. One of the problems <br>
with duration based effects is stacking and negating the need for multiple <br>
characters of the same class. I am designing these spells with that in <br>
mind. If you want to 100% ensure an NPC does not gate you will need <br>
more than one wizard<br>
<br>
Demented One Said<br>
Great one more Useless Mana Sucking Agro Building Waste of space in my <br>
Spell book, I need to med three new spells to keep a monster from gating <br>
in all the raids I have been on only 1 in 60 mobs stay alive long enough <br>
to get a gate off. and the tanks already can do this its call bash Bards can <br>
do it with charm, ENchanter can do it will Mana Drain or Mezz and Now wizards can<br>
do it too it takes three wizard spells to do what any other class can do in one.<br>
GREAT FIX THERE MR.POE <br>
<br>
MR. Poe Said<br>
I think not only does it fit in<br>
well with wizards being the masters of arcane transportation<br>
<br>
<br>
Demented One Said<br>
Funny when I signed on it said WIZARD's were the masters of Arcane DAMAGE<br>
When did I become a taxi MR. Poe... I don't remember seeing an Email about it<br>
or a fax or even a post card. Heck my EverQuest BOOK that your company Printer <br>
STILL SAYS Wizard's MASTERS of ARCANE DAMAGE. <br>
NO where in my book does it say you need a TAXI licence to Play a WIZARD.<br>
<br>
